TITLE      Production of 97Ru and 103Ru radionuclide from
            alpha-induced reaction on natMo
AUTHOR     (M.Upadhyay, M.Choudhary, N.Singh, A.Gandhi, P.Dubey,
            S.Dasgupta, J.Datta, Y.N.Kopatch, I.N.Ruskov,
            A.Kumar)
INSTITUTE  (3INDBHU,3RUMBUC,3INDVEC,4ZZZDUB,3BULBLA)
REFERENCE  (J,JRN,334,6423,2025)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,3INDVEC) K-130 cyclotron
SAMPLE     natMo of (99.95% purity, 12.50 +/- 0.12 um thick,
            12.80 +/- 0.10 mg wt.).
            The natCu (10.11 +/- 0.11 um thick,
            9.01 +/- 0.10 mg wt.) acted as a catcher and monitor
            foil and natAl of thickness 25.00 +/- 0.25 um as an
            energy degrader.
DETECTOR   (HPGE) Detector of 40% relative efficiency.
METHOD     (STTA,ACTIV) The stack was irradiated for ~18 hr with
            a beam current of 120 nA.
